The article is a speech given by Dr. Jill Biden in Greensboro, NC at North Carolina A&T as part of Secretary Cardona's Road to Success tour. Dr. Biden discusses the importance of recruiting, respecting, and retaining teachers. She emphasizes the need for more diverse educators who can understand and support students of color. Dr. Biden also mentions President Biden's commitment to education and his efforts to recruit more people into the teaching profession and provide resources for educators. She encourages individuals who feel called to become teachers and highlights the positive impact they can have on students' lives. The speech concludes with an introduction of Secretary of Education, Miguel Cardona.